&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fully remote | Complete engagement job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in Palo Alto by Dr. Andrew Ng and Israel Niezen, Factored helps U.S. companies build and scale world-class AI, ML, and Data teams, powered by the top 1% of LATAM talent, with a defining purpose:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;To empower brilliant humans, unleash their potential, and amplify their impact in the world.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Factored, you’ll be part of a community that values learning, ownership, and authenticity, where your growth is personal and your ideas matter. We’re transparent, curious, and collaborative. We strive for excellence, celebrate diversity, encourage curiosity, and build an environment where you can truly thrive.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Forward Deployed ML/AI Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;, you will bridge the gap between cutting-edge AI research and robust, production-grade applications. You will be responsible for the end-to-end lifecycle of intelligent systems, from data ingestion and model training to deployment. This role requires deep technical proficiency in training and tuning classical machine learning models (such as gradient-boosted trees, random forests, and regression suites) alongside modern Generative AI architectures, including Large Language Models (LLMs), retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) pipelines, and agentic workflows. You will design scalable APIs, optimize model inference latency, and architect full-stack infrastructure to ensure AI capabilities are seamlessly delivered to end-users.&lt;br&gt;You are both a technical builder and a strategic business partner, embedded within customer environments to deliver measurable AI outcomes. You will bridge the gap between cutting-edge AI research and robust, production-grade applications while serving as a translator between technical capabilities and business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your mission goes beyond model development—you will own the end-to-end delivery of intelligent systems that directly impact customer business metrics. You will design scalable APIs, optimize model inference, architect infrastructure, AND guide executive stakeholders through complex technical decisions. You will identify high-impact opportunities where machine learning can drive efficiency or unlock new product capabilities, working collaboratively across customer organizations (technical, product, operations, and business teams) to ensure solutions deliver real, measurable business value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires exceptional ability to navigate ambiguity, build trust with diverse stakeholders, and operate effectively in fast-paced, cross-functional customer environments where you&#39;ll often be the most technical person in the room—yet must communicate that expertise clearly to non-technical decision-makers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Functional Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Stakeholder Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Translate complex business requirements into technical AI specifications in collaboration with product, operations, and business teams. Serve as the technical authority on AI/ML topics while remaining approachable to non-technical stakeholders. Manage expectations, communicate risks transparently, and maintain stakeholder confidence through complex projects. Lead alignment discussions when technical constraints conflict with business priorities. Coordinate with customer teams to ensure end-to-end delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Problem Definition &amp;amp; Solution Architecture: &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with customer leadership to clearly define business problems, success metrics, and constraints. Structure ambiguous problems into clear technical requirements with explicit trade-off analysis. Present multiple solution approaches with pros/cons

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fully remote | Complete engagement job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in Palo Alto by Dr. Andrew Ng and Israel Niezen, Factored helps U.S. companies build and scale world-class AI, ML, and Data teams, powered by the top 1% of LATAM talent, with a defining purpose:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;To empower brilliant humans, unleash their potential, and amplify their impact in the world.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Factored, you’ll be part of a community that values learning, ownership, and authenticity, where your growth is personal and your ideas matter. We’re transparent, curious, and collaborative. We strive for excellence, celebrate diversity, encourage curiosity, and build an environment where you can truly thrive.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for Factored&#39;s first Product Manager for the Business Transformation &amp;amp; Intelligence (BTI) team. You will build the internal technology—the workflows, data infrastructure, and tools to empower our teams to do their best work. You’ll sit at the intersection of vision and execution, transforming manual, reactive processes into an autonomous, self-serve intelligence ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Problem Solving &amp;amp; Continuous Curiosity:&lt;/strong&gt; Go beyond ticket completion. Investigate root causes and stakeholder pain points to build intentional, high-impact solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agile Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead with high agency, breaking down ambiguous goals into actionable, incremental tasks. Define the &quot;what&quot; and &quot;why,&quot; partnering closely with engineering on the &quot;how.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transparent Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Act with honesty and humility. Vocalize blockers early, provide candid feedback on processes, and maintain a rigorous balance between designing with intention and fiercely advocating for our users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sustainable Delivery:&lt;/strong&gt; Prioritize clean, well-documented, and scalable practices. Balance rapid delivery with craftsmanship to ensure the long-term reliability of our systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Servant Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Embody empathy in all interactions. Mentor teammates, guide new users, and democratize solutions to ensure the team succeeds together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Proactively communicate the product roadmap, current work-in-progress, and recent launches to provide broad visibility and alignment across internal teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to Factored:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of product management, project management, or similar experience, ideally in technical, data, or software environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven end-to-end product ownership, from initial discovery to launch and iteration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to mentor junior PMs and establish scalable product processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in Agile workflows (e.g., Jira, Linear) and in technical architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills for translating business priorities into actionable specs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;UX/UI sensibility, strong attention to detail, including wireframing, and a user-first mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;While it’s not required, it’s an added plus if you also have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with decentralized data mesh, predictive ML talent matching, or analytics products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in HR tech, recruiting tools, or talent platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&qu

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fully remote | Complete engagement job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in Palo Alto by Dr. Andrew Ng and Israel Niezen, Factored helps U.S. companies build and scale world-class AI, ML, and Data teams, powered by the top 1% of LATAM talent, with a defining purpose:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;To empower brilliant humans, unleash their potential, and amplify their impact in the world.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Factored, you’ll be part of a community that values learning, ownership, and authenticity, where your growth is personal and your ideas matter. We’re transparent, curious, and collaborative. We strive for excellence, celebrate diversity, encourage curiosity, and build an environment where you can truly thrive.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a strategic and results-driven &lt;strong&gt;Senior Project Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the planning, execution, and delivery of high-impact, complex projects. You will be responsible for the full project lifecycle, ensuring that technical and business objectives are met while driving high-level strategy and cross-functional alignment. This position is ideal for a seasoned leader who excels at managing ambiguity, mitigating risk, and mentoring teams to deliver excellence at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Functional Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end project delivery (from scope definition to final release) ensuring every client project is completed on time, within budget, and at the expected quality bar.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define clear, measurable goals and deliverables in collaboration with senior leadership, and remain personally accountable for hitting them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the single go-to person for the client across the full project lifecycle — managing expectations proactively, communicating status and risks with clarity, and ensuring the client&#39;s voice is reflected in every key decision. Build trust through consistency, transparency, and follow-through.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive delivery using agile principles: planning and facilitating sprints, managing the release calendar, coordinating go/no-go decisions, and adapting plans iteratively based on client feedback and changing requirements. Ensure each release is well-scoped, tested, and communicated to all stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead engineering teams with a hands-on approach: unblocking impediments in real time, running effective standups and steering meetings, and maintaining high team velocity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and resolve conflicts before they escalate into blockers. Mediate disagreements with clarity and fairness, and develop robust contingency plans for both technical and operational risks throughout the project lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and actively manage comprehensive project plans — including timelines, and resource allocation — for large-scale initiatives. Maintain executive-level visibility through steering committee meetings, surfacing critical risks and recommending strategic pivots when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee and manage the integration of client requirements into the broader roadmap, ensuring long-term compliance and value delivery without compromising scope or timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and refine PMO methodologies, agile frameworks, and best practices that raise operational excellence across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze project performance data to extract actionable insights on profitability, ROI, and lessons learned, feeding them back into future initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s in Business, Engineering, or a related field; PMP, PRINCE2, or Agile (CSM) certifications are strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

